      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOLD MEDLEY JUJON NZ (1) was at the tail of the field when resuming at Menangle but came from a much wider barrier. Had strong city form last time in. Fitter and should enjoy an economical run from the ace draw so expect big improvement. RED SAPPHIRE (10) has been good in two Menangle outings since a spell, finishing runner-up fresh before coming from a wide barrier and finishing 6.5 metres away last Saturday. Draws out a little on the second line but strikes at 50 per cent here and should be close to peak fitness. ITZMINEONTHELINE (8) worked from a  similar barrier but did a good job to battle on for third here on Monday. HARLEEQUIN (7) has placed in all three previous third-up attempts and has a strong record at this circuut and distance.",
